1
00:00:01,393 --> 00:00:04,115
Two weeks ago, an
invisible dome crashed down

2
00:00:04,116 --> 00:00:07,392
on Chester's Mill, cutting us
off from the rest of the world.

3
00:00:07,481 --> 00:00:10,117
Why the dome is here or
what mysteries lie ahead,

4
00:00:10,118 --> 00:00:11,385
we still don't know.

5
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:13,787
Every day it tests our limits,

6
00:00:13,788 --> 00:00:17,022
bringing out the best and the worst in us.

7
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:20,493
Some say we'll be stuck here forever,

8
00:00:20,494 --> 00:00:25,616
but we will never stop
fighting to find a way out.

9
00:00:25,617 --> 00:00:28,719
Rebecca Pine thinks Chester's
Mill can't sustain itself

10
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:30,186
for much longer and she and Jim

11
00:00:30,187 --> 00:00:33,023
want to use the census to
decide who lives and who doesn't.

12
00:00:33,024 --> 00:00:35,191
That pig virus is their extermination plan.

13
00:00:35,192 --> 00:00:37,127
Yeah, and she doesn't
know how strong it is.

14
00:00:37,128 --> 00:00:38,594
Get away from me!

15
00:00:38,595 --> 00:00:40,430
You tried to kill us all.

16
00:00:40,431 --> 00:00:41,731
What are you doing here?

17
00:00:41,732 --> 00:00:43,333
She's joining you in jail.

18
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:46,403
- What are you gonna do to us?
- Tomorrow, we'll have a town meeting,

19
00:00:46,404 --> 00:00:47,703
and the people can decide your fate.

20
00:00:47,704 --> 00:00:49,839
You've come to set me free.

21
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:52,008
My mother said you have
answers. I want them.

22
00:00:52,009 --> 00:00:55,210
- This is it, right?
- Sorry, kid.

23
00:00:55,211 --> 00:00:56,812
Those are the fingertips of a hand.

24
00:00:56,813 --> 00:01:00,181
Looks like Angie got a piece
of whoever did this to her.

25
00:01:01,784 --> 00:01:03,886
What do you say, Phil?

26
00:01:03,887 --> 00:01:06,422
Can I count on you?

27
00:01:06,423 --> 00:01:09,925
I am Melanie Cross.

28
00:01:09,926 --> 00:01:12,826
And I think this is where I died.

29
00:01:19,148 --> 00:01:20,669
Oh, my God, we have to help her.

30
00:01:20,670 --> 00:01:22,003
I don't think we can.

31
00:01:22,004 --> 00:01:24,504
- It's too late.
- She's dying.

32
00:01:33,615 --> 00:01:35,650
What are you doing?

33
00:01:35,651 --> 00:01:36,582
You were moaning.

34
00:01:37,343 --> 00:01:38,577
Nightmare?

35
00:01:38,578 --> 00:01:40,578
No. Just a dream.

36
00:01:40,579 --> 00:01:44,482
Not as scary as waking up
to you two standing over me.

37
00:01:44,483 --> 00:01:47,085
None of us sleep very well these days.

38
00:01:47,086 --> 00:01:50,221
I need to find Sam Verdreaux.

39
00:01:50,222 --> 00:01:52,556
Find out what really
happened the night I died.

40
00:01:52,557 --> 00:01:54,892
I know you want some answers,

41
00:01:54,893 --> 00:01:56,794
but we promised Barbie
we wouldn't do anything

42
00:01:56,795 --> 00:01:58,861
until after he talks to Julia.

43
00:01:59,830 --> 00:02:02,165
- I need to talk to you.
- I have to find our mystery girl.

44
00:02:02,166 --> 00:02:05,168
- She didn't come home last night.
- Melanie stayed with Joe and Norrie.

45
00:02:05,169 --> 00:02:07,471
Melanie? How do you know her name?

46
00:02:07,472 --> 00:02:09,439
It's a long story.

47
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:11,909
You wouldn't happen to know
where Sam is, would you?

48
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:14,777
He just left.

49
00:02:14,778 --> 00:02:16,279
We were up all night, working.

50
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,680
Why are you looking for Sam?

51
00:02:17,681 --> 00:02:20,683
Because I think he's known
who Melanie is all along.

52
00:02:20,684 --> 00:02:22,119
All right, tell me everything.

53
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:25,922
The kids found her picture
in the school yearbook.

54
00:02:25,923 --> 00:02:28,625
- So, she's a student here?
- Was.

55
00:02:28,626 --> 00:02:30,326
In 1988.

56
00:02:30,327 --> 00:02:32,294
I know.

57
00:02:32,295 --> 00:02:34,497
I'm still processing all of this.

58
00:02:34,498 --> 00:02:39,802
She also knows exactly where Joe
and Norrie found the mini-dome.

59
00:02:39,803 --> 00:02:42,438
- How?
- 25 years ago, she and

60
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:44,440
three of her friends found a meteorite

61
00:02:44,441 --> 00:02:46,642
in exactly the same spot in the woods

62
00:02:46,643 --> 00:02:48,144
with an egg inside.

63
00:02:48,145 --> 00:02:49,912
Melanie said that when she found it,

64
00:02:49,913 --> 00:02:52,915
that she wanted to protect
it, and the others got violent.

65
00:02:52,916 --> 00:02:55,617
And then, one of her friends killed her.

66
00:02:55,618 --> 00:02:57,619
She's not sure who.

67
00:02:57,620 --> 00:02:59,088
Who were the three friends?

68
00:02:59,089 --> 00:03:02,958
Pauline Verdreaux, Lyle Chumley

69
00:03:02,959 --> 00:03:04,893
and Sam.

70
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:06,442
This is crazy.

71
00:03:06,443 --> 00:03:09,565
This is just par for the
course for Chester's Mill.

72
00:03:09,566 --> 00:03:12,534
And we need to talk about
what happened the other day.

73
00:03:12,535 --> 00:03:15,704
About your supporting Jim and
Rebecca's extermination plot?

74
00:03:15,705 --> 00:03:18,073
How could you think that
I would actually do that?

75
00:03:18,074 --> 00:03:20,308
- Because I was there.
- I was listening

76
00:03:20,309 --> 00:03:22,944
so I could make sure that I knew
exactly what they were up to,

77
00:03:22,945 --> 00:03:24,312
so I could stop them.

78
00:03:24,313 --> 00:03:26,581
I made Jim look me in the eye

79
00:03:26,582 --> 00:03:28,849
and promise me that he
wasn't gonna do anything.

80
00:03:28,850 --> 00:03:31,018
I don't know that I believe that.

81
00:03:31,019 --> 00:03:32,987
If you want to think that I'm the bad guy,

82
00:03:32,988 --> 00:03:34,989
then fine.

83
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:39,358
Be prepared to think far
worse of Sam Verdreaux.

84
00:04:12,558 --> 00:04:14,594
What the hell are you doing?

85
00:04:14,595 --> 00:04:17,063
Trying to find what
you've been hiding from me.

86
00:04:17,064 --> 00:04:19,099
Like my mom's journal.

87
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,366
I don't have it, Junior.

88
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:21,735
Someone stole it.

89
00:04:21,736 --> 00:04:23,036
That was Lyle.

90
00:04:23,037 --> 00:04:24,370
Lyle's in jail.

91
00:04:24,371 --> 00:04:26,239
He was until I snuck him out.

92
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,475
He told me my mom's journal
had predictions in it,

93
00:04:29,476 --> 00:04:31,577
like who was gonna kill Angie.

94
00:04:31,578 --> 00:04:32,911
What'd you find out?

95
00:04:32,912 --> 00:04:34,747
I didn't get that far. He attacked me,

96
00:04:34,748 --> 00:04:37,544
and he ran off with it. He didn't
want me to see what was in it.

97
00:04:38,485 --> 00:04:40,552
So he must have killed Angie, right?

98
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:44,555
He always has been a little nuts.

99
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:48,226
Pages missing from the journal.

100
00:04:48,227 --> 00:04:50,495
I thought if I'd find it, I'd be able

101
00:04:50,496 --> 00:04:53,598
to figure out where he's going
or what he's gonna do next, or

102
00:04:53,599 --> 00:04:55,134
where he would run off to.

103
00:04:55,135 --> 00:04:56,434
You won't find anything.

104
00:04:56,435 --> 00:04:58,370
If Lyle hurts somebody else, it's on me.

105
00:04:58,371 --> 00:05:00,071
So we'll stop him together.

106
00:05:02,074 --> 00:05:04,709
I should have never trusted
him, no matter what my mom said.

107
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:07,544
Your mother told you to trust Lyle?

108
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,881
Before she died?

109
00:05:11,784 --> 00:05:14,751
Two days ago, she sent me an e-mail.

110
00:05:16,287 --> 00:05:18,990
She's alive.

111
00:05:18,991 --> 00:05:21,793
She's out there somewhere.

112
00:05:23,128 --> 00:05:25,063
I was wondering when you two would show.

113
00:05:25,064 --> 00:05:26,998
Yeah, we're just looking
for Carolyn and the kids.

114
00:05:26,999 --> 00:05:28,666
Oh, in the back.

115
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:31,302
I can bring you cereal, toast and tea.

116
00:05:31,303 --> 00:05:33,470
Where'd you get all the food?

117
00:05:33,471 --> 00:05:35,038
Secret store in the basement.

118
00:05:35,039 --> 00:05:37,208
Angie told me about it, God rest her soul.

119
00:05:37,209 --> 00:05:41,444
Oh, and we're all waiting
for the town meeting, Julia.

120
00:05:43,314 --> 00:05:45,349
If she's eating here, I ain't.

121
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,283
Hey, it's a free town.

122
00:05:47,284 --> 00:05:48,752
Not since Big Jim went to jail.

123
00:05:48,753 --> 00:05:50,053
I hear you right, Greg?

124
00:05:50,054 --> 00:05:51,454
You throwing your lot in with the guy

125
00:05:51,455 --> 00:05:52,689
who tried to murder everyone

126
00:05:52,690 --> 00:05:53,790
with that virus of his?

127
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:55,325
Jim wasn't caught with no virus.

128
00:05:55,326 --> 00:05:57,060
It was a set-up, all
right, so she can take over

129
00:05:57,061 --> 00:05:58,428
- and put him on trial.
- Get off!

130
00:05:58,429 --> 00:05:59,996
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!
- That's enough. Hey,

131
00:05:59,997 --> 00:06:01,964
just back off.

132
00:06:03,966 --> 00:06:06,369
This trial of yours?

133
00:06:06,370 --> 00:06:08,837
It better reach the right verdict.

134
00:06:12,141 --> 00:06:13,409
Did you find Lyle?

135
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:16,512
Not yet. Junior and I
spent all night combing

136
00:06:16,513 --> 00:06:18,349
the town for him, but no sign of him.

137
00:06:18,350 --> 00:06:19,815
I should be out there looking for him.

138
00:06:19,816 --> 00:06:21,050
This place is a powder keg.

139
00:06:21,051 --> 00:06:23,318
No, I want the three
of you to lie low today.

140
00:06:23,319 --> 00:06:24,887
This trial has to happen soon.

141
00:06:24,888 --> 00:06:27,656
I'm planning on reading the
charges against Jim and Rebecca

142
00:06:27,657 --> 00:06:28,791
at the town meeting.

143
00:06:28,792 --> 00:06:31,093
They'll need representation, too.

144
00:06:31,094 --> 00:06:33,194
Which is where you come in, I hope?

145
00:06:33,996 --> 00:06:35,464
Mom as Big Jim's lawyer?

146
00:06:35,465 --> 00:06:37,499
He's so totally guilty.

147
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,301
Everyone deserves a fair trial.

148
00:06:39,302 --> 00:06:40,469
Well, I guess I'll go,

149
00:06:40,470 --> 00:06:43,639
uh, escort my new clients to the town hall.

150
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,641
I'll see you there, Julia.

151
00:06:45,642 --> 00:06:48,510
Thank you, Carolyn.

152
00:06:48,511 --> 00:06:49,811
I filled Julia in

153
00:06:49,812 --> 00:06:52,046
on everything that we
found out about Melanie,

154
00:06:52,047 --> 00:06:53,181
but only Julia.

155
00:06:53,182 --> 00:06:54,883
I'm really sorry that I wasn't there

156
00:06:54,884 --> 00:06:56,151
with you yesterday, Melanie.

157
00:06:56,152 --> 00:06:58,419
I know who I am now,

158
00:06:58,420 --> 00:07:01,389
but why am I back?

159
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:04,325
I don't know, but there is a reason.

160
00:07:04,326 --> 00:07:06,227
I promise I'll find out what it is.

161
00:07:06,228 --> 00:07:07,862
Sam will be at the town hall.

162
00:07:07,863 --> 00:07:09,563
Barbie and I will talk to him.

163
00:07:09,564 --> 00:07:11,766
All right, but he's right.

164
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:13,534
You kids stay. Okay?

165
00:07:13,535 --> 00:07:16,002
Let us get some answers first.

166
00:07:17,271 --> 00:07:20,174
I just found out I died.

167
00:07:20,175 --> 00:07:22,510
I can't just sit around and do nothing.

168
00:07:22,511 --> 00:07:25,145
Come on, I know where to go.

169
00:07:25,146 --> 00:07:27,181
Hey!

170
00:07:27,182 --> 00:07:28,615
Anybody out there?

171
00:07:28,616 --> 00:07:30,818
Okay, enough, Jim. I've got a headache.

172
00:07:30,819 --> 00:07:33,053
Oh, you got a headache, huh?

173
00:07:33,054 --> 00:07:34,454
I'm just about starving in here.

174
00:07:34,455 --> 00:07:37,390
Come on. It's only been one night.

175
00:07:37,391 --> 00:07:38,525
Julia promised a trial.

176
00:07:38,526 --> 00:07:39,693
She'll come for us, okay?

177
00:07:39,694 --> 00:07:41,829
Yeah, she'll come for us, all right.

178
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,863
Then what?

179
00:07:43,864 --> 00:07:46,264
She gonna hang us?

180
00:07:47,266 --> 00:07:49,803
We were just trying to keep
everyone from starving to death.

181
00:07:49,804 --> 00:07:52,305
Now everyone thinks I'm
some sort of serial killer,

182
00:07:52,306 --> 00:07:53,940
and it's all your fault.

183
00:07:53,941 --> 00:07:56,042
You convinced me that your
plan's the right thing to do.

184
00:07:56,043 --> 00:07:58,478
And then you... then you tricked
me into not being able to do it.

185
00:07:58,479 --> 00:07:59,712
I told you,

186
00:07:59,713 --> 00:08:01,780
the virus was stronger than I thought.

187
00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:04,550
If the evidence changes,
your thinking has to change.

188
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:06,085
It's called science.

189
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:07,987
I don't care what you call it.

190
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,390
Now everybody's out there for our blood.

191
00:08:11,391 --> 00:08:13,792
Thanks, everyone, for joining me today.

192
00:08:13,793 --> 00:08:16,161
I know it's been a rough week,

193
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:19,732
but I think it's time for
us to focus on our future.

194
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:21,467
Where's that piece of crap... Big Jim?

195
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:23,802
He and Rebecca Pine will be arraigned

196
00:08:23,803 --> 00:08:25,871
and tried in front of a jury.

197
00:08:25,872 --> 00:08:28,407
The process will be fair and impartial.

198
00:08:28,408 --> 00:08:31,410
First, though, I'd like to talk
to you about the food situation.

199
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:33,278
Supplies are running low.

200
00:08:34,813 --> 00:08:36,481
But there's no need to panic.

201
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:38,816
We can get through this by coming together.

202
00:08:38,817 --> 00:08:42,888
Which is why I'm initiating a
voluntary food share program.

203
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:44,522
People can bring whatever they have

204
00:08:44,523 --> 00:08:46,557
to the Chester's Mill fire station.

205
00:08:46,558 --> 00:08:48,659
Volunteers will oversee distribution,

206
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,761
insuring no one goes hungry.

207
00:08:49,762 --> 00:08:51,362
You want me to give up

208
00:08:51,363 --> 00:08:52,864
my family's food? That's crazy!

209
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:55,299
Participation is completely voluntary.

210
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,534
But pooling our resources

211
00:08:56,535 --> 00:08:59,570
is the best way to
insure everyone gets fed.

212
00:08:59,571 --> 00:09:02,440
There's the son of a bitch!

213
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:04,308
Why'd you try to kill us all, Jim?

214
00:09:04,309 --> 00:09:07,511
Everything I did, I did for this town.

215
00:09:09,514 --> 00:09:12,582
I love Chester's Mill,

216
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:15,152
and I'll prove that I'm
innocent of these charges.

217
00:09:15,153 --> 00:09:17,254
Good luck, honey.

218
00:09:18,856 --> 00:09:21,792
Today, we arraign Jim
Rennie and Rebecca Pine

219
00:09:21,793 --> 00:09:24,060
- on the following charges.
- It's all lies!

220
00:09:24,061 --> 00:09:25,529
You deserve to be on trial, not him!

221
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:26,696
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

222
00:09:30,468 --> 00:09:33,136
Folks, calm down and let her speak.

223
00:09:33,137 --> 00:09:36,304
Calm down! Back up. Let her speak.

224
00:09:38,288 --> 00:09:39,809
Phil, you got to get them out of here!

225
00:09:39,810 --> 00:09:43,112
Big Jim, Rebecca, let's go.

226
00:09:43,113 --> 00:09:45,348
Gun!

227
00:10:05,634 --> 00:10:08,036
He's dead.

228
00:10:27,511 --> 00:10:31,805
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

229
00:10:35,949 --> 00:10:38,377
I just can't believe Pauline's still alive.

230
00:10:38,378 --> 00:10:39,293
Why would she let us

231
00:10:39,294 --> 00:10:40,763
believe that she was dead for so long,

232
00:10:40,764 --> 00:10:43,031
- even if she was protecting us?
- You were a kid.

233
00:10:43,032 --> 00:10:46,369
Maybe you needed protecting. I didn't.

234
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:49,905
When Pauline started
ranting about some dome,

235
00:10:49,906 --> 00:10:51,774
I stopped believing in her.

236
00:10:51,775 --> 00:10:53,575
It crushed her.

237
00:10:53,576 --> 00:10:55,210
But what kind of person

238
00:10:55,211 --> 00:10:58,519
lets her brother and her
son spend a decade mourning,

239
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:01,054
while she sends postcards
to her insane ex-boyfriend?

240
00:11:01,055 --> 00:11:02,923
And not warning us about the people

241
00:11:02,924 --> 00:11:04,224
who were really gonna die,

242
00:11:04,225 --> 00:11:05,458
like Angie.

243
00:11:05,459 --> 00:11:07,727
If I could just get to her,

244
00:11:07,728 --> 00:11:08,895
things would be different.

245
00:11:08,896 --> 00:11:12,397
She'd tell me if I was
doing the right thing.

246
00:11:13,266 --> 00:11:16,236
When I lost Mom,

247
00:11:16,237 --> 00:11:18,918
it was the worst pain ever.

248
00:11:18,919 --> 00:11:20,553
Until Angie.

249
00:11:20,554 --> 00:11:23,389
Lyle took the best thing I had.

250
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:26,392
And when I find him, I'm
gonna make him suffer.

251
00:11:26,393 --> 00:11:29,395
Right before I put a
bullet between his eyes.

252
00:11:29,396 --> 00:11:32,164
You know what, kid?

253
00:11:32,165 --> 00:11:34,700
Maybe those missing journal pages

254
00:11:34,701 --> 00:11:36,002
are the key to finding Lyle.

255
00:11:36,003 --> 00:11:38,637
I've been looking for 'em everywhere.

256
00:11:38,638 --> 00:11:41,266
I might know a place.

257
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:43,569
You only have yourself to blame.

258
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:45,337
You and Jim

259
00:11:45,338 --> 00:11:48,640
and your insane reduction
plan has people terrified.

260
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:50,809
We're lucky only Wendell died today.

261
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,411
Anybody could have been hit, a kid

262
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:54,480
or me or you.

263
00:12:03,455 --> 00:12:06,456
Thank you.

264
00:12:07,659 --> 00:12:10,595
Just so you know...

265
00:12:10,596 --> 00:12:14,499
what Jim said about Barbie being involved,

266
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,501
he wasn't.

267
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:19,537
We went behind his back.

268
00:12:19,538 --> 00:12:23,005
Barbie always believed
there was another way.

269
00:12:27,545 --> 00:12:29,880
- Phil, stop.
- Why? I don't answer to you.

270
00:12:29,881 --> 00:12:32,249
Yes, you do. This town put me in charge.

271
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,684
Well, Big Jim made me sheriff.

272
00:12:33,685 --> 00:12:35,519
And when people are at risk, I act.

273
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:37,721
You could have just arrested Wendell.

274
00:12:37,722 --> 00:12:39,430
Barbie had already disarmed
him. Instead you killed him.

275
00:12:39,431 --> 00:12:42,126
I did what I had to do
to keep this town safe.

276
00:12:42,127 --> 00:12:44,495
Wendell is dead. Not to mention
the fact that Lyle escaped

277
00:12:44,496 --> 00:12:46,364
on your watch and is still on the loose.

278
00:12:46,365 --> 00:12:49,032
Maybe that badge is too big for you.

279
00:12:50,001 --> 00:12:52,069
You want me to quit?

280
00:12:53,104 --> 00:12:56,039
- You gonna make me?
- No, not her.

281
00:12:56,674 --> 00:12:59,076
Me.

282
00:13:03,281 --> 00:13:05,516
You two...

283
00:13:05,517 --> 00:13:08,419
really are drunk on power, huh?

284
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:11,087
We'll see what Big Jim has to say.

285
00:13:15,093 --> 00:13:16,960
If you'd been sheriff
today instead of Phil,

286
00:13:16,961 --> 00:13:18,428
- no one would've been killed.
- Julia...

287
00:13:18,429 --> 00:13:19,797
You have the perfect background.

288
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:22,299
- Your military training...
- A... and a few hours ago

289
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:24,301
you accused me of siding with Big Jim.

290
00:13:24,302 --> 00:13:26,170
Now you want me to be the person in charge

291
00:13:26,171 --> 00:13:27,769
of keeping him locked up?

292
00:13:32,109 --> 00:13:34,275
I should have trusted you.

293
00:13:35,779 --> 00:13:37,380
I'm sorry I didn't.

294
00:13:37,381 --> 00:13:39,781
That's good to hear.

295
00:13:40,917 --> 00:13:44,354
This town just has a funny
way of turning on people,

296
00:13:44,355 --> 00:13:48,223
and I'm not ready to
jump back into the fray.

297
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:53,196
I get it.

298
00:13:53,197 --> 00:13:56,498
I'll find someone else.

299
00:13:56,499 --> 00:13:58,034
I'm gonna go.

300
00:13:58,035 --> 00:14:00,169
Lyle's still out there.

301
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:02,338
- Maybe he's with Sam.
- Yeah, well,

302
00:14:02,339 --> 00:14:04,240
we'll find 'em, we'll
put 'em in a room together

303
00:14:04,241 --> 00:14:06,339
and find out what the hell
happened all those years ago.

304
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,443
We have to.

305
00:14:07,444 --> 00:14:08,877
For Melanie's sake.

306
00:14:08,878 --> 00:14:11,478
Yeah.

307
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:14,282
So when you touch the
dome, it shows you stuff?

308
00:14:14,283 --> 00:14:15,551
Yeah.

309
00:14:15,552 --> 00:14:16,952
Like, visions, I guess.

310
00:14:16,953 --> 00:14:18,454
Seriously?

311
00:14:18,455 --> 00:14:21,256
Hey, you told us you
died and we got on board.

312
00:14:21,257 --> 00:14:22,891
Have some team spirit.

313
00:14:22,892 --> 00:14:25,626
But what if it shows me something awful?

314
00:14:25,627 --> 00:14:29,263
You'll get over it. We have.

315
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,201
When you touch the dome for the first time,

316
00:14:33,202 --> 00:14:36,204
it's gonna give you a little shock.

317
00:14:36,205 --> 00:14:37,906
So if you get scared,

318
00:14:37,907 --> 00:14:40,306
just let go.

319
00:15:01,661 --> 00:15:03,529
What do you see?

320
00:15:04,164 --> 00:15:06,367
Nothing.

321
00:15:06,368 --> 00:15:09,535
Absolutely nothing.

322
00:15:12,806 --> 00:15:14,354
You sure about this?

323
00:15:14,355 --> 00:15:17,023
I already searched this place pretty good.

324
00:15:17,024 --> 00:15:19,758
I've known Lyle a long time.

325
00:15:20,794 --> 00:15:24,730
Guy's got a lot of tricks up his sleeve.

326
00:15:33,506 --> 00:15:35,041
Well, what do you know?

327
00:15:35,042 --> 00:15:38,343
You found 'em.

328
00:15:38,978 --> 00:15:40,046
See?

329
00:15:40,047 --> 00:15:42,982
Your mom did draw Angie.

330
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:44,984
Lyle stole these to keep
me from knowing what he did.

331
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:46,852
But... but why kill Angie?

332
00:15:46,853 --> 00:15:48,521
He hardly knew her.

333
00:15:48,522 --> 00:15:51,724
Maybe this has something to do with it?

334
00:15:51,725 --> 00:15:53,759
- The four hands.
- The four hands.

335
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:56,361
Pauline ranted about a
lot of things: pink stars,

336
00:15:56,362 --> 00:15:58,697
a dome that would trap
us and the four hands

337
00:15:58,698 --> 00:16:00,399
that would be its protectors.

338
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:03,535
She used to say, "Four
hands will hold up the dome,

339
00:16:03,536 --> 00:16:05,270
and without them, it will fall."

340
00:16:05,271 --> 00:16:07,506
Like if one of the hands wasn't around,

341
00:16:07,507 --> 00:16:09,373
the dome would come down?

342
00:16:11,043 --> 00:16:13,078
That's why Lyle did it.

343
00:16:13,079 --> 00:16:15,613
He killed Angie to bring down the dome.

344
00:16:15,614 --> 00:16:18,283
So Angie was one of the four hands?

345
00:16:18,284 --> 00:16:22,385
Maybe all four hands have
to die for it to work.

346
00:16:23,788 --> 00:16:25,557
I have to go.

347
00:16:25,558 --> 00:16:27,358
I have to make sure the
other hands are okay.

348
00:16:27,359 --> 00:16:28,860
The other hands?

349
00:16:28,861 --> 00:16:30,294
Do you know who they are?

350
00:16:30,295 --> 00:16:31,963
Yeah.

351
00:16:31,964 --> 00:16:33,598
Joe, Norrie and me.

352
00:16:33,599 --> 00:16:35,866
If Lyle thinks that killing the four hands

353
00:16:35,867 --> 00:16:37,768
will bring down the dome,

354
00:16:37,769 --> 00:16:40,169
any one of us could be next.

355
00:16:49,152 --> 00:16:50,620
Hey, Jim?

356
00:16:50,621 --> 00:16:53,189
Uh-huh.

357
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:55,525
You ever seen a man die?

358
00:16:55,526 --> 00:16:57,527
I mean...

359
00:16:57,528 --> 00:17:00,997
before today?

360
00:17:00,998 --> 00:17:04,934
It's a sad fact of my
life that I have, yeah.

361
00:17:04,935 --> 00:17:06,870
So...

362
00:17:06,871 --> 00:17:08,704
how do you...

363
00:17:08,705 --> 00:17:11,040
deal with it?

364
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:15,843
Just by knowing it's all
part of a larger design.

365
00:17:16,579 --> 00:17:21,016
Wendell's death means we get to live.

366
00:17:21,017 --> 00:17:23,252
I'm sure that's a pretty good trade-off.

367
00:17:23,253 --> 00:17:28,323
That... that's what I told
myself about our population plan.

368
00:17:28,324 --> 00:17:30,760
But today...

369
00:17:30,761 --> 00:17:33,828
watching the life go out of Wendell...

370
00:17:33,829 --> 00:17:37,099
Death isn't pretty, Rebecca.

371
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:39,768
Sometimes it's necessary.

372
00:17:39,769 --> 00:17:42,104
I've always looked at things clinically.

373
00:17:42,105 --> 00:17:45,573
Run tests, you get results
and then take action.

374
00:17:46,174 --> 00:17:48,410
I thought it made me strong.

375
00:17:48,411 --> 00:17:50,611
But?

376
00:17:51,132 --> 00:17:53,267
When I was in the church yesterday,

377
00:17:53,268 --> 00:17:57,171
about to release the virus,
and I saw those families,

378
00:17:57,172 --> 00:17:59,974
it reminded me of my mom.

379
00:17:59,975 --> 00:18:04,045
And when I thought about causing
all those families to suffer

380
00:18:04,046 --> 00:18:06,446
the way she did, I...

381
00:18:07,882 --> 00:18:10,183
That's why you couldn't do it?

382
00:18:11,819 --> 00:18:13,420
What if my dad was right

383
00:18:13,421 --> 00:18:15,756
and sometimes there really aren't answers?

384
00:18:15,757 --> 00:18:17,791
Well, maybe your dad is right.

385
00:18:17,792 --> 00:18:21,295
That doesn't mean we stop trying.

386
00:18:21,296 --> 00:18:25,499
Look, I trusted you.

387
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,167
I had your back.

388
00:18:27,168 --> 00:18:29,535
I need you to have mine.

389
00:18:30,170 --> 00:18:32,205
You're right.

390
00:18:32,206 --> 00:18:34,707
I... I do.

391
00:18:38,445 --> 00:18:40,312
Big Jim!

392
00:18:46,853 --> 00:18:49,254
Drinking on the job, Sheriff?

393
00:18:50,790 --> 00:18:52,759
Nope.

394
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:53,860
'Cause Julia fired me.

395
00:18:53,861 --> 00:18:57,029
I had to sneak past my own
deputies to get in here.

396
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:59,298
Oh, well...

397
00:18:59,299 --> 00:19:02,033
that ain't right.

398
00:19:06,472 --> 00:19:08,840
You're a good man, Phil.

399
00:19:11,377 --> 00:19:15,781
The best sheriff this town's ever had.

400
00:19:15,782 --> 00:19:17,582
Better than Duke?

401
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,717
And Linda.

402
00:19:20,719 --> 00:19:23,688
Your plan to release that virus...

403
00:19:23,689 --> 00:19:27,091
you had no other choice, right?

404
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,361
I didn't even have the virus.

405
00:19:30,362 --> 00:19:31,962
Rebecca did.

406
00:19:33,432 --> 00:19:35,767
But if we don't do something,

407
00:19:35,768 --> 00:19:38,703
then none of us are gonna
get out of here alive.

408
00:19:38,704 --> 00:19:40,939
And now Julia's made you her scapegoat.

409
00:19:42,442 --> 00:19:45,375
Right when this town needed you most.

410
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:48,778
Wait, wait, wait. No, no, no. Not that way.

411
00:19:50,281 --> 00:19:52,616
Half this town hates me, okay?

412
00:19:52,617 --> 00:19:55,019
If, uh, you let me out, they're gonna...

413
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:57,188
they're gonna string me up.

414
00:19:57,189 --> 00:19:59,256
Then how do we make this right?

415
00:19:59,958 --> 00:20:04,761
We got to win over their hearts and minds.

416
00:20:07,932 --> 00:20:10,601
- Still nothing.
- The dome kind of has a mind of its own.

417
00:20:10,602 --> 00:20:12,436
Maybe it's not in the mood.

418
00:20:12,437 --> 00:20:15,673
What if we try touching
it at the same time?

419
00:20:15,674 --> 00:20:16,858
Worked for me and Norrie.

420
00:20:16,884 --> 00:20:19,509
Because you guys aren't
some kind of undead freak.

421
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:21,178
Melanie, we're gonna figure this out.

422
00:20:21,179 --> 00:20:22,279
How long will that take?

423
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:25,248
I still have no idea why I'm back.

424
00:20:25,249 --> 00:20:27,384
None of us know why we're
trapped inside this fishbowl.

425
00:20:27,385 --> 00:20:29,252
You need to deal.

426
00:20:29,253 --> 00:20:31,821
Think of it this way:
you were alive, then dead,

427
00:20:31,822 --> 00:20:33,290
now alive again.

428
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:34,364
Two out of three ain't bad.

429
00:20:34,365 --> 00:20:36,433
You don't know what I'm going through.

430
00:20:36,434 --> 00:20:38,167
No, I don't.

431
00:20:38,168 --> 00:20:42,305
But I know how much I'd give
to have my mom alive again.

432
00:20:42,306 --> 00:20:44,407
If it'd bring her back, I'd trade

433
00:20:44,408 --> 00:20:48,409
you rotting in the bottom of
that crater in a heartbeat.

434
00:20:53,215 --> 00:20:55,617
You know, I've defended you a lot,

435
00:20:55,618 --> 00:20:58,787
but sometimes you're a real bitch.

436
00:20:58,788 --> 00:21:01,189
Melanie, wait!

437
00:21:05,995 --> 00:21:08,730
Joe?!

438
00:21:08,731 --> 00:21:10,831
Norrie?! Are you guys here?

439
00:21:17,172 --> 00:21:18,540
They aren't here either.

440
00:21:18,541 --> 00:21:20,075
Maybe we should head back to Julia's.

441
00:21:20,076 --> 00:21:21,276
They weren't there.

442
00:21:21,277 --> 00:21:23,111
Or at the Sweetbriar or
anywhere else in town.

443
00:21:23,112 --> 00:21:25,046
What if Lyle already got 'em?

444
00:21:25,047 --> 00:21:27,482
If he hurts them, I won't
be able to forgive myself.

445
00:21:27,483 --> 00:21:29,050
Junior, like I said before,

446
00:21:29,051 --> 00:21:31,252
there's no way Lyle could know
they're part of the four hands.

447
00:21:31,253 --> 00:21:32,720
Your friends are safe.

448
00:21:32,721 --> 00:21:34,089
What are you looking for?

449
00:21:34,090 --> 00:21:36,358
You got to take a minute and calm down.

450
00:21:36,359 --> 00:21:39,159
You're no good to anyone in this state.

451
00:21:41,562 --> 00:21:44,098
You haven't had a drink
since the dome came down.

452
00:21:44,099 --> 00:21:45,432
You sure you want to do this?

453
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:47,201
My dead sister's alive,

454
00:21:47,202 --> 00:21:49,203
my nephew's on some nutball's hit list.

455
00:21:49,204 --> 00:21:52,706
Yeah, I want to do this.

456
00:22:12,192 --> 00:22:14,559
Another one?

457
00:22:17,731 --> 00:22:19,331
Melanie.

458
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,036
Melanie.

459
00:22:23,037 --> 00:22:24,704
You got to understand,

460
00:22:24,705 --> 00:22:29,442
- about Norrie...
- It's not her, it's me.

461
00:22:29,443 --> 00:22:33,246
I want to be happy, but...

462
00:22:33,247 --> 00:22:36,748
I feel so alone.

463
00:22:39,217 --> 00:22:41,886
And I'm not normal, either.

464
00:22:43,556 --> 00:22:45,923
You're normal to me.

465
00:22:58,537 --> 00:22:59,671
Didn't find your answers

466
00:22:59,672 --> 00:23:01,906
touching the Dome, hey, maybe
you'll find 'em by sticking

467
00:23:01,907 --> 00:23:03,194
your tongue down his throat.

468
00:23:03,195 --> 00:23:04,839
Actually, what I'm wondering is what he

469
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:06,975
sees in you, since you
treat him and everyone else

470
00:23:06,976 --> 00:23:08,608
like crap.

471
00:23:16,150 --> 00:23:19,153
Hey, stop.

472
00:23:19,154 --> 00:23:20,321
Norrie, are you okay?

473
00:23:20,322 --> 00:23:21,556
Don't even, Joe.

474
00:23:21,557 --> 00:23:23,023
You're bleeding.

475
00:23:25,893 --> 00:23:27,028
And you're about to be.

476
00:23:27,029 --> 00:23:28,029
Hey, hey.

477
00:23:28,030 --> 00:23:31,197
I've got an idea.

478
00:23:32,366 --> 00:23:35,235
Here we go.

479
00:23:37,071 --> 00:23:38,439
Food drive's doing well.

480
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:40,007
Yeah, I mean, it's a decent turnout,

481
00:23:40,008 --> 00:23:42,074
but for this to work...

482
00:23:42,910 --> 00:23:44,144
... we need everyone's help.

483
00:23:44,145 --> 00:23:47,781
I'm gonna put these in the fridge.

484
00:23:49,684 --> 00:23:52,019
Oh, can you stack those boxes?

485
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:53,652
Yes.

486
00:24:41,167 --> 00:24:43,667
Carolyn.

487
00:24:50,609 --> 00:24:51,743
Where's Julia?

488
00:24:51,744 --> 00:24:53,611
Still inside.

489
00:24:56,449 --> 00:24:57,716
Julia!

490
00:24:57,717 --> 00:24:59,282
Over here.

491
00:25:04,956 --> 00:25:07,357
Come on.

492
00:25:14,332 --> 00:25:16,034
Go!

493
00:25:45,052 --> 00:25:47,721
As soon as it's safe to enter the building,

494
00:25:47,722 --> 00:25:50,090
we will assess the
damage, see what remains.

495
00:25:50,091 --> 00:25:51,859
The last of my food was in there.

496
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:53,469
What's my family supposed to eat tonight?

497
00:25:53,470 --> 00:25:55,362
Please, I just need everyone to stay calm.

498
00:25:55,363 --> 00:25:59,132
- Don't tell us to stay calm.
- Hey, Phil, watch yourself.

499
00:25:59,133 --> 00:26:00,299
So I can't even speak now?

500
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:02,400
These people need to know the truth.

501
00:26:03,035 --> 00:26:04,404
Julia's big plan...

502
00:26:04,405 --> 00:26:06,639
was just a way to take
everybody's food away from them.

503
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:09,229
- I didn't take anything.
- Then she sticks it all in one place,

504
00:26:09,230 --> 00:26:10,543
along with an old, beat-up generator.

505
00:26:10,544 --> 00:26:11,711
Now, if she had bothered to check,

506
00:26:11,712 --> 00:26:14,614
she would have seen that
the wires were frayed.

507
00:26:14,615 --> 00:26:16,916
Big Jim never would have made that mistake.

508
00:26:16,917 --> 00:26:18,684
And now we're all gonna starve.

509
00:26:18,685 --> 00:26:20,253
What am I gonna feed my kids?

510
00:26:20,254 --> 00:26:22,098
- Where am I gonna get food tomorrow?
- All... all right,

511
00:26:22,099 --> 00:26:24,493
I promise I will get to
the bottom of what happened

512
00:26:24,494 --> 00:26:25,995
and find a solution.

513
00:26:25,996 --> 00:26:29,164
I just need everyone to calm down.

514
00:26:35,003 --> 00:26:36,704
This is not over.

515
00:26:56,324 --> 00:26:58,024
Hey.

516
00:26:59,210 --> 00:27:01,612
You okay?

517
00:27:02,613 --> 00:27:04,482
We're screwed.

518
00:27:04,483 --> 00:27:06,884
And Phil's right, it's all my fault.

519
00:27:06,885 --> 00:27:08,052
I didn't check the generators,

520
00:27:08,053 --> 00:27:10,187
I didn't even think to check.

521
00:27:10,188 --> 00:27:12,790
And I screwed up with you.

522
00:27:12,791 --> 00:27:14,357
I should have believed you.

523
00:27:17,628 --> 00:27:19,864
That goes both ways. Do you hear me?

524
00:27:19,865 --> 00:27:22,199
We both made mistakes.

525
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,999
What now?

526
00:27:28,372 --> 00:27:30,506
Now we figure out who caused the explosion.

527
00:27:31,542 --> 00:27:33,277
Phil said the wires were frayed.

528
00:27:33,278 --> 00:27:34,911
You don't believe him?

529
00:27:34,912 --> 00:27:36,146
No, there's something else

530
00:27:36,147 --> 00:27:37,747
going on. I found a bunch of empty boxes

531
00:27:37,748 --> 00:27:39,683
right before that explosion.

532
00:27:39,684 --> 00:27:41,618
There's only one person
in town who could do that.

533
00:27:41,619 --> 00:27:44,967
Well, I'd ask who that was,
but it's a little obvious.

534
00:27:45,759 --> 00:27:47,227
I'll go talk with Big Jim.

535
00:27:47,228 --> 00:27:49,129
I just wish I knew what to do.

536
00:27:49,130 --> 00:27:51,065
You know, no matter what, I can't seem

537
00:27:51,066 --> 00:27:53,292
to please more than
half the town at a time.

538
00:27:53,318 --> 00:27:54,257
Hey, shh, shh.

539
00:27:59,239 --> 00:28:00,974
Don't give up.

540
00:28:00,975 --> 00:28:03,810
There's a way out of
this. You're gonna find it.

541
00:28:03,811 --> 00:28:06,878
Okay?

542
00:28:23,562 --> 00:28:25,095
You okay?

543
00:28:32,904 --> 00:28:34,840
Ow.

544
00:28:34,841 --> 00:28:36,441
Sorry.

545
00:28:37,443 --> 00:28:38,477
No, please,

546
00:28:38,478 --> 00:28:39,910
let me.

547
00:28:42,313 --> 00:28:45,951
- Aah.
- So what's this gonna show?

548
00:28:45,952 --> 00:28:48,152
Hopefully if there are
differences between us.

549
00:28:48,153 --> 00:28:53,024
A guy who's always been
alive, like me, and...

550
00:28:53,025 --> 00:28:55,059
someone like you.

551
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:56,360
Are we different?

552
00:28:56,361 --> 00:28:58,228
Uh, not sure.

553
00:28:58,229 --> 00:29:00,430
Little out of my depth here.

554
00:29:00,431 --> 00:29:01,632
Ms. Pine would

555
00:29:01,633 --> 00:29:03,367
definitely be able to
tell us what this means.

556
00:29:03,368 --> 00:29:05,735
So, what, we break her out of jail?

557
00:29:05,736 --> 00:29:06,936
I'm just saying.

558
00:29:06,937 --> 00:29:08,938
She tried to kill everyone in town.

559
00:29:08,939 --> 00:29:11,141
We can't just do nothing.

560
00:29:11,142 --> 00:29:14,044
This blood thing could
be the answer to who I am.

561
00:29:14,045 --> 00:29:16,146
Yeah, or end up like everything else...

562
00:29:16,147 --> 00:29:18,547
big, fat, dead end.

563
00:29:26,973 --> 00:29:28,374
Well, well, well.

564
00:29:28,375 --> 00:29:31,310
Look who it is. You sheriff by now?

565
00:29:31,311 --> 00:29:33,913
Or did new Queen Bee just
go ahead and anoint you

566
00:29:33,914 --> 00:29:36,282
- king of Chester's Mill?
- Oh, shut your mouth, Jim.

567
00:29:36,283 --> 00:29:38,284
There's no audience down here.

568
00:29:38,285 --> 00:29:41,287
There was an explosion at the firehouse.

569
00:29:41,288 --> 00:29:42,755
All the food that was stored there's gone.

570
00:29:42,756 --> 00:29:45,358
You think I'd put this town at risk

571
00:29:45,359 --> 00:29:47,326
by burning up its food supply?

572
00:29:47,327 --> 00:29:49,462
That's a new level of crazy, Barbie,

573
00:29:49,463 --> 00:29:51,863
even for you.

574
00:29:53,298 --> 00:29:56,268
Oh, my God.

575
00:29:56,269 --> 00:29:58,137
Phil.

576
00:29:58,138 --> 00:30:01,306
He was down here grousing
about Julia taking

577
00:30:01,307 --> 00:30:03,175
his badge and he mentioned something

578
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:04,442
about the food program.

579
00:30:04,443 --> 00:30:05,744
So that's how you're gonna play this?

580
00:30:05,745 --> 00:30:07,345
You're gonna throw Phil under the bus?

581
00:30:07,346 --> 00:30:11,348
Well, don't take my word
for it, ask... ask Rebecca.

582
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:32,436
I must have been asleep when Phil came in.

583
00:30:32,437 --> 00:30:34,638
I didn't hear anything.

584
00:30:42,313 --> 00:30:43,547
Nice try, Jim.

585
00:30:43,548 --> 00:30:47,518
Fine. You're gonna go about your day

586
00:30:47,519 --> 00:30:49,687
thinking I'm responsible for the explosion,

587
00:30:49,688 --> 00:30:51,888
that's, you know...

588
00:30:51,889 --> 00:30:54,391
Just be ready for whatever...

589
00:30:54,392 --> 00:30:58,127
madness Phil has planned next.

590
00:31:27,890 --> 00:31:29,024
Phil?

591
00:31:29,025 --> 00:31:31,459
What are you doing in here?

592
00:31:32,228 --> 00:31:34,628
Just making sure the place is secure.

593
00:31:35,164 --> 00:31:37,599
Is there food in there?

594
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:40,000
We weren't using this room.

595
00:31:41,871 --> 00:31:44,373
Maybe someone moved it.

596
00:31:44,374 --> 00:31:47,409
Why would they?

597
00:31:47,410 --> 00:31:50,945
Unless they knew the explosion was coming?

598
00:32:10,431 --> 00:32:13,234
My mom lied to everyone.

599
00:32:13,235 --> 00:32:15,103
The only one she loves is Lyle.

600
00:32:15,104 --> 00:32:17,238
I hear you, buddy.

601
00:32:17,239 --> 00:32:19,207
And they're both crazy.

602
00:32:19,208 --> 00:32:21,374
They're crazying it up together.

603
00:32:22,276 --> 00:32:23,911
You got to sleep this one off.

604
00:32:23,912 --> 00:32:26,378
Mm-hmm.

605
00:32:42,129 --> 00:32:44,497
I don't want to do this to you.

606
00:32:46,699 --> 00:32:49,101
You or Angie.

607
00:32:49,669 --> 00:32:50,770
If there was any other way

608
00:32:50,771 --> 00:32:53,239
to bring the Dome down, I'd do it.

609
00:32:58,878 --> 00:33:01,279
I'm sorry.

610
00:33:11,391 --> 00:33:13,724
Thanks for looking out for me.

611
00:33:15,161 --> 00:33:18,696
You're the only family I have left.

612
00:33:20,399 --> 00:33:23,201
Love you, Uncle Sam.

613
00:33:39,284 --> 00:33:41,252
Hey, on the ground.

614
00:33:41,253 --> 00:33:43,121
Get on the ground right now.

615
00:33:43,122 --> 00:33:46,391
No, Barbie, that's what you're gonna do.

616
00:33:46,392 --> 00:33:47,592
Oh, come on, this is not you, Phil.

617
00:33:47,593 --> 00:33:50,061
I know you don't want to hurt anyone.

618
00:34:08,746 --> 00:34:10,180
Drop her, Phil.

619
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:11,581
You're done being the hero, Barbie.

620
00:34:14,318 --> 00:34:16,452
Drop... now!

621
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:26,163
You all right?

622
00:34:26,164 --> 00:34:27,564
Yeah.

623
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:29,131
You?

624
00:34:29,666 --> 00:34:32,169
I am now.

625
00:34:50,682 --> 00:34:52,350
Julia.

626
00:34:52,351 --> 00:34:53,818
What a nice surprise.

627
00:34:53,819 --> 00:34:55,887
Do you have a minute?

628
00:34:55,888 --> 00:34:58,193
I'm just wondering about what's happening

629
00:34:58,194 --> 00:34:59,594
at the Sweetbriar Rose.

630
00:34:59,595 --> 00:35:03,631
I see you there, feeding
everyone, and, uh...

631
00:35:03,632 --> 00:35:05,400
I wonder where the food is coming from.

632
00:35:05,401 --> 00:35:07,266
The basement pantry.

633
00:35:08,002 --> 00:35:10,136
I just checked there... it's empty.

634
00:35:10,905 --> 00:35:13,408
Andrea, you're doing an amazing job.

635
00:35:13,409 --> 00:35:15,610
The town continues to live because of you.

636
00:35:15,611 --> 00:35:19,812
I just think I owe it to
everyone to at least ask.

637
00:35:20,981 --> 00:35:23,816
There's something I have to show you.

638
00:35:31,959 --> 00:35:34,494
Oh, my God.

639
00:35:35,729 --> 00:35:37,597
This is just the start.

640
00:35:37,598 --> 00:35:41,234
The entire basement is filled.

641
00:35:41,235 --> 00:35:42,669
There's enough to feed the whole
town for a couple of months.

642
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:44,938
Where did you get all this food?

643
00:35:44,939 --> 00:35:46,840
From Lloyd, my late husband.

644
00:35:46,841 --> 00:35:48,942
Lloyd called himself a survivalist.

645
00:35:48,943 --> 00:35:51,845
He always saw something
bad around the corner.

646
00:35:51,846 --> 00:35:53,579
Thank God.

647
00:35:53,580 --> 00:35:55,181
Said when the crisis hit,

648
00:35:55,182 --> 00:35:57,449
it'd be every man for himself.

649
00:35:59,118 --> 00:36:00,920
I'm sorry I didn't come forward.

650
00:36:00,921 --> 00:36:05,023
I was just scared someone
would steal it from me.

651
00:36:06,192 --> 00:36:08,094
But I trust you.

652
00:36:08,095 --> 00:36:11,396
You should use it.

653
00:36:11,397 --> 00:36:14,098
We'll use it together.

654
00:36:33,250 --> 00:36:35,552
Uncle Sam?

655
00:36:38,356 --> 00:36:42,593
My mom painted that when
I was in the second grade.

656
00:36:42,594 --> 00:36:44,728
I brought it in for show-and-tell.

657
00:36:44,729 --> 00:36:48,197
I'm guessing you've never seen this before.

658
00:36:55,539 --> 00:36:58,008
Oh, my God.

659
00:36:58,009 --> 00:36:59,442
The obelisk.

660
00:36:59,443 --> 00:37:01,478
I saw this in a dream I had.

661
00:37:01,479 --> 00:37:02,813
My mom was there, too.

662
00:37:02,814 --> 00:37:04,547
"1821."

663
00:37:04,548 --> 00:37:06,082
That's the number of the locker at school

664
00:37:06,083 --> 00:37:07,250
where Angie got killed.

665
00:37:07,251 --> 00:37:09,919
It's also in your mother's
journal, on the last page.

666
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:11,354
I had no idea what it meant.

667
00:37:11,355 --> 00:37:15,390
Lyle saw something in the
journal before he ran off.

668
00:37:16,493 --> 00:37:18,028
Maybe he went back to the locker.

669
00:37:18,029 --> 00:37:19,229
Why would he go there?

670
00:37:19,230 --> 00:37:20,730
I don't know, but it obviously

671
00:37:20,731 --> 00:37:23,098
means something to him.

672
00:37:23,099 --> 00:37:25,768
Maybe we haven't found Lyle
'cause we haven't checked there.

673
00:37:35,444 --> 00:37:36,846
This is amazing.

674
00:37:36,847 --> 00:37:39,881
It's like Thanksgiving in July.

675
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:41,750
It's all Julia.

676
00:37:41,751 --> 00:37:42,784
Where'd you get the food?

677
00:37:42,785 --> 00:37:43,985
Trade secret.

678
00:37:43,986 --> 00:37:45,220
But make sure to thank Andrea

679
00:37:45,221 --> 00:37:47,755
for hosting such a lovely event.

680
00:37:49,358 --> 00:37:51,326
One nice meal doesn't prove anything.

681
00:37:51,327 --> 00:37:52,594
You're no Big Jim.

682
00:37:52,595 --> 00:37:54,596
Well...

683
00:37:54,597 --> 00:37:56,764
I'll let him decide that.

684
00:38:03,638 --> 00:38:05,740
What the hell are we doing here?

685
00:38:05,741 --> 00:38:09,077
Oh, just wait and see.

686
00:38:09,078 --> 00:38:11,912
Folks, I, uh, said this morning

687
00:38:11,913 --> 00:38:13,981
that I thought it was time for us Millers

688
00:38:13,982 --> 00:38:15,516
to focus on our future.

689
00:38:15,517 --> 00:38:20,054
But I don't think we can do
that until we let go of the past.

690
00:38:20,055 --> 00:38:23,757
Even the actions of
those who have wronged us.

691
00:38:23,758 --> 00:38:26,727
What Big Jim and Rebecca
tried to do yesterday

692
00:38:26,728 --> 00:38:28,662
is inexcusable...

693
00:38:29,764 --> 00:38:33,266
... but it's not unforgivable.

694
00:38:34,434 --> 00:38:36,503
Now, we can stay angry,

695
00:38:36,504 --> 00:38:39,506
tear each other apart, or...

696
00:38:39,507 --> 00:38:41,742
we can rise above,

697
00:38:41,743 --> 00:38:44,144
and... and work together,

698
00:38:44,145 --> 00:38:48,880
and ensure our survival under this dome.

699
00:38:53,553 --> 00:38:57,357
I admit...

700
00:38:57,358 --> 00:39:00,827
I've made some mistakes...

701
00:39:00,828 --> 00:39:04,196
but all of them in service of this town.

702
00:39:04,197 --> 00:39:07,299
And I really appreciate Julia

703
00:39:07,300 --> 00:39:10,569
giving me the chance to...

704
00:39:10,570 --> 00:39:12,704
to make amends.

705
00:39:15,675 --> 00:39:19,009
And you all should know...

706
00:39:22,047 --> 00:39:26,451
... I think she's done a hell
of a job running Chester's Mill.

707
00:39:56,782 --> 00:39:58,650
Enjoy yourself. Enjoy yourself, folks.

708
00:39:58,651 --> 00:40:00,550
Enjoy the food.

709
00:40:01,952 --> 00:40:03,854
You know, I don't understand you.

710
00:40:03,855 --> 00:40:05,956
You keep saying you're on my side,

711
00:40:05,957 --> 00:40:07,925
but it sure as hell seems
like you've turned on me.

712
00:40:07,926 --> 00:40:10,861
I just think, maybe...

713
00:40:10,862 --> 00:40:13,130
we should give Julia a chance.

714
00:40:13,131 --> 00:40:17,301
Maybe benevolence isn't such
a bad quality in a leader.

715
00:40:17,302 --> 00:40:20,938
Or it's the thing that's
gonna get us all killed.

716
00:40:20,939 --> 00:40:22,406
Look what you did.

717
00:40:22,407 --> 00:40:24,708
Yeah, it wouldn't have
happened without you.

718
00:40:24,709 --> 00:40:27,244
Oh, I don't know about that.

719
00:40:27,245 --> 00:40:29,446
Have you... you found your sheriff yet?

720
00:40:29,447 --> 00:40:31,582
Why, you have someone in mind?

721
00:40:31,583 --> 00:40:33,183
I might.

722
00:40:55,039 --> 00:40:57,473
I'm sorry about earlier.

723
00:40:57,474 --> 00:40:58,708
You kissed her, Joe.

724
00:40:58,709 --> 00:41:01,009
Yeah, but...

725
00:41:01,010 --> 00:41:03,445
she's not who I love.

726
00:41:04,213 --> 00:41:05,548
You are.

727
00:41:05,549 --> 00:41:06,915
That's your go-to...

728
00:41:06,916 --> 00:41:10,184
after you've macked on another
chick in front of my face?

729
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:13,622
Try it on her.

730
00:41:13,623 --> 00:41:16,790
She's dumb enough to fall for it.

731
00:41:23,900 --> 00:41:25,533
Hi.

732
00:41:27,070 --> 00:41:30,739
Julia... I'm impressed.

733
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:33,441
Especially with what
you did for Jim and me.

734
00:41:33,442 --> 00:41:35,176
I did what was best for the town.

735
00:41:35,177 --> 00:41:37,612
I just wanted to say thank you.

736
00:41:37,613 --> 00:41:40,214
Julia, we've got a
quick question back here.

737
00:41:44,487 --> 00:41:48,122
Joe says you're really, really smart.

738
00:41:48,123 --> 00:41:50,057
Like a scientist.

739
00:41:50,058 --> 00:41:51,425
Thank you.

740
00:41:51,426 --> 00:41:53,895
I have something I want you to figure out.

741
00:41:53,896 --> 00:41:56,529
About me.

742
00:42:17,819 --> 00:42:20,386
Junior? What are you doing?

743
00:42:20,387 --> 00:42:21,955
This is where Angie died.

744
00:42:21,956 --> 00:42:24,490
It meant something to the killer.

745
00:42:34,600 --> 00:42:37,437
Looks like the whole
thing's been kicked in.

746
00:42:37,438 --> 00:42:39,738
Give me your flashlight.

747
00:42:41,106 --> 00:42:43,175
It's big enough for a man.

748
00:42:43,176 --> 00:42:45,177
Do you think this is
where Lyle disappeared to?

749
00:42:45,178 --> 00:42:47,279
It's a tunnel.

750
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,380
Yeah, but to where?

751
00:42:56,679 --> 00:43:04,381
